\f0\fs24 \cf0 # FluxPrompt API Integration Guide\
\
This document captures everything learned from integrating three FluxPrompt AI flows into a production React + Express application. Follow it exactly and you will avoid every issue we hit during development.\
\
---\
\
## Authentication\
\
All requests use a single API key passed as a **request header** \'97 not a query param, not a Bearer token.\
\
```\
Header name:  api-key\
Header value: <your key>\
```\
\
Store the key in an environment variable. In Vite/React projects use `VITE_FLUXPROMPT_API_KEY` (prefix required for Vite's env exposure). In Node/Express use `FLUXPROMPT_API_KEY`.\
\
```ts\
const apiKey = import.meta.env.VITE_FLUXPROMPT_API_KEY; // client\
const apiKey = process.env.FLUXPROMPT_API_KEY;          // server\
```\
\
---\
\
## Base URL\
\
```\
https://api.fluxprompt.ai/flux/api-v2\
```\
\
Append `?flowId=<FLOW_ID>` as a query parameter. For session-aware flows, also append `&sessionId=<SESSION_ID>`.\
\
```\
https://api.fluxprompt.ai/flux/api-v2?flowId=9bacf2bb-9b5c-42a7-ad52-8cedb3eba05d&sessionId=my-session-abc\
```\
\
---\
\
## Request Format\
\
Every request is a `POST` with `Content-Type: application/json`. The body always has this shape:\
\
```json\
\{\
  "variableInputs": [\
    \{ "inputId": "varInputNode_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXX_X.XXXX", "inputText": "..." \},\
    \{ "inputId": "varInputNode_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXX_X.XXXX", "inputText": "..." \}\
  ]\
\}\
```\
\
**Critical rules:**\
- `variableInputs` is an ordered array \'97 order matters for some flows.\
- Every `inputId` must match exactly what the flow expects. Wrong IDs produce no error \'97 the input is silently ignored and the flow returns a canned/default response.\
- All values are strings. Even numeric parameters (temperature, max_tokens) are serialized as a JSON-fragment string (see Model Parameters section).\
- Missing inputs do not throw an HTTP error. They produce incorrect AI behavior or a guardrail response. Always send all expected inputs.\
\
---\
\
## The Three Flows\
\
### Flow 1 \'97 Chat Model (Session-Aware)\
\
**Use for:** Multi-turn conversation, case analysis sessions, anything that needs persistent chat memory.\
\
```\
Flow ID:   9bacf2bb-9b5c-42a7-ad52-8cedb3eba05d\
Session:   Required \'97 append &sessionId=<unique-slug> to the URL\
Inputs:    5\
```\
\
| # | inputId | Purpose |\
|---|---------|---------|\
| 1 | `varInputNode_1773364131277_0.8862` | User's message text |\
| 2 | `varInputNode_1773434271666_0.6770` | Document / image context |\
| 3 | `varInputNode_1773434287086_0.5082` | Model parameters (JSON fragment) |\
| 4 | `varInputNode_1773434416738_0.6139` | System prompt |\
| 5 | `varInputNode_1773450743306_0.1255` | Image analysis mode (`"yes"` or `"no"`) |\
\
**Full example body:**\
\
```json\
\{\
  "variableInputs": [\
    \{\
      "inputId": "varInputNode_1773364131277_0.8862",\
      "inputText": "What are the key financial discrepancies in this document?"\
    \},\
    \{\
      "inputId": "varInputNode_1773434271666_0.6770",\
      "inputText": "Documents in session:\\n1. FinancialRecords_2023.pdf\\n\\nImage references:\\nhttps://yourdomain.com/uploads/exhibit-a.jpg"\
    \},\
    \{\
      "inputId": "varInputNode_1773434287086_0.5082",\
      "inputText": "  \\"temperature\\": 0.3,\\n  \\"max_tokens\\": 10024,\\n  \\"chat_template_kwargs\\": \{\\n        \\"enable_thinking\\": false\\n      \},\\n  \\"thinking_token_budget\\": 1028"\
    \},\
    \{\
      "inputId": "varInputNode_1773434416738_0.6139",\
      "inputText": "You are an advanced legal analysis assistant..."\
    \},\
    \{\
      "inputId": "varInputNode_1773450743306_0.1255",\
      "inputText": "no"\
    \}\
  ]\
\}\
```\
\
**Session ID rules:**\
- Use any stable slug tied to the user's chat session (e.g. `case-1234-user-56`).\
- The same `sessionId` across requests gives the model memory of prior turns.\
- Different `sessionId` values start a completely fresh context.\
- Do not reuse session IDs across different users.\
\
---\
\
### Flow 2 \'97 General Model (Stateless)\
\
**Use for:** One-off tasks \'97 document classification, summarization, prompt evaluation, admin jobs, anything that does not need conversation memory.\
\
```\
Flow ID:   26c06cfd-7f7e-423c-ae32-4c290aaef45e\
Session:   Not used \'97 omit sessionId from the URL entirely\
Inputs:    4\
```\
\
| # | inputId | Purpose |\
|---|---------|---------|\
| 1 | `varInputNode_1773364131277_0.8862` | Task / question |\
| 2 | `varInputNode_1773434271666_0.6770` | Document or data context |\
| 3 | `varInputNode_1773434287086_0.5082` | Model parameters (JSON fragment, no thinking_token_budget) |\
| 4 | `varInputNode_1773434416738_0.6139` | System prompt |\
\
**Full example body:**\
\
```json\
\{\
  "variableInputs": [\
    \{\
      "inputId": "varInputNode_1773364131277_0.8862",\
      "inputText": "Classify the sentiment of this customer complaint."\
    \},\
    \{\
      "inputId": "varInputNode_1773434271666_0.6770",\
      "inputText": "The service was completely unacceptable and I want a refund."\
    \},\
    \{\
      "inputId": "varInputNode_1773434287086_0.5082",\
      "inputText": "  \\"temperature\\": 0.3,\\n  \\"max_tokens\\": 8024,\\n  \\"chat_template_kwargs\\": \{\\n        \\"enable_thinking\\": false\\n      \}"\
    \},\
    \{\
      "inputId": "varInputNode_1773434416738_0.6139",\
      "inputText": "You are a smart assistant."\
    \}\
  ]\
\}\
```\
\
Note: the model parameters for this flow do **not** include `thinking_token_budget`. Including it may cause unexpected behavior.\
\
